dudleya viren , green bright green dudleya , uncommon species perennial , succulent plant family crassulaceae , native california baja california , grow los angeles county , channel islands , guadalupe island . 
leaf fleshy strap-shaped , 8-20 cm long 1.5-3 cm broad , taper base near middle mostly green . 
arrange rosette . 
flower white , five petal 7-10 mm long ; produce april , may , june . 
hummingbird visit flower nectar . 
grow best full sun light shade inland , prefer well-drained soil . 
